node_9.description: This is Katie Adams's plan for Monday February 13: 9:00 am - Wake up and complete morning routine, including shower and getting dressed., 10:00 am - Head to Hobbs Cafe for breakfast and socializing with friends., 11:00 am - Attend cheerleading practice and work on routines., 1:00 pm - Have lunch at the campus cafeteria with teammates, discussing plans for the week., 2:00 pm - Attend classes and focus on studies for the day., 5:00 pm - Finish classes and head back to Hobbs Cafe for a coffee and to catch up with friends., 6:00 pm - Have dinner, either at home or in the cafeteria, depending on the mood., 7:00 pm - Spend some time on campus socializing and flirting with the other girls about the new male student., 8:30 pm - Organize a small gathering with friends to discuss how to approach getting to know the new male student better., 11:00 pm - Get ready for a party at a friend's apartment, excited to see who will show interest in the new guy., 2:00 am - Return home and prepare for bed..
